latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Being a fashion influencer, wearing different outfits & styling them has been a part of my journey, but I’ve always been judged for it. Whether it’s provocative clothing or a different style, undeniably - judgement has been a part of my process. 

I am very thankful to @JustHumanIndia who gave me this opportunity to put my story of discrimination  out in the world. This movement started by them is a great initiative and I hope they can reach out to everyone who has faced prejudice of any sorts. 
You can tell your story of discrimination too by using the hashtag #Iamjusthuman.

latestPosts.caption:
#WeddingSutraOnLocation at @azafashions store, Mehrauli, New Delhi.

Blogger and bride-to-be @drishtigwalani explored Aza Fashions' latest bridal collection and found the perfect outfits for her Sangeet and Pheras.

First, she chose a pastel #Roqa lehenga set, beautifully adorned with pink  embroidery, sequins, and katdana details. The look is completed with an embroidered blouse and a free-flowing dupatta.

For the wedding look, she picked a classic red lehenga by #RimpleandHarpreet, featuring a red tulle fabric with a choli. The lehenga showcases an intricate all-over gold jaal, interspersed with geometric motifs inspired by art deco, crafted using maradi ka kaam and highlighted with sequins and pearls, all topped off with a delicate tulle dupatta.

If you'd like to be part of our upcoming editorial shoots, DM us at +91 98925 23796.

Venue: @azafashions
Makeup Artist: @makeupbymeghnaroda
Photographer: @beginnings_for_you
